[4] What is the difference between a Fork and a Pull Request? Answer in 2 lines.
=>  A Fork is a personal copy of someone else's repository created under your own GitHub account, allowing you to freely make changes without affecting the original project.
    A Pull Request is a request you send to the original repository's owner asking them to review and merge your changes from your forked or branched version back into the main project.


